SIMPLE: whelm
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whelm
<hw>Whelm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Whelmed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Whelming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>whelmen</ets> to turn
over, akin to OE. <ets>whelven</ets>, AS. <ets>whelfan</ets>,
<ets>hwylfan</ets>, in <ets><?/whylfan</ets>, <ets><?/whelfan</ets>, to
overwhelm, cover over; akin to OS. <ets>bihwelbian</ets>, D.
<ets>welven</ets> to arch, G. <ets>w⟦oum⟧lben</ets>, OHG.
<ets>welben</ets>, Icel. <ets>hvelfa</ets> to overturn; cf. Gr. <?/
bosom, a hollow, a gulf.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To cover with water or other fluid; to cover by
immersion in something that envelops on all sides; to overwhelm; to
ingulf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She is my prize, or ocean <qex>whelm</qex> them all!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>whelming</qex> billow and the faithless oar.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: To cover completely, as if with water; to
immerse; to overcome; <as>as, to <ex>whelm</ex> one in
sorrows</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>whelming</xex> weight of
crime.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. H. Newman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To throw (something) over a thing so as to cover
it.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whelp</ent>⟦br⟧
